\begin{abstract}
\noindent The central role of neutrinos in the determination of fundamental interactions is reviewed. The recent SuperKamiokande discovery of neutrino mass gives an {\it aper\c cu} of physics at short distances, and tests theories of flavor.   
Quark-lepton symmetries, derived from  grand unification and/or string
theories, can help determine the  standard model parameters in the neutrino sector.

\end{abstract
